Are Actually Richest for Research\n\n**Task:** Split the overnight `OUTSIDE_ACTIVE_HOURS` blocked sample by hour so we can stop treating overnight as one lump and instead identify which hour is structurally richest for future research or shadow expansion.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- Hour-by-hour overnight structure is meaningfully different:\n  - `00h`: count `47`, mean `30.73`, median `35.8`, strong-bias share `34.0%`, pos `40`, neg `7`\n  - `01h`: count `60`, mean `-0.84`, median `-2.15`, strong-bias share `40.0%`, pos `30`, neg `30`\n  - `02h`: count `46`, mean `-36.66`, median `-39.1`, strong-bias share `41.3%`, pos `5`, neg `41`\n  - `03h`: count `57`, mean `-22.25`, median `-35.4`, strong-bias share `42.1%`, pos `18`, neg `39`\n- This means overnight is not one regime:\n  - `00h` is mostly positive-skewed\n  - `01h` is balanced / mixed\n  - `02h` is the cleanest bearish-skew hour\n  - `03h` has the highest strong-bias density of the overnight hours\n- Wrote breakdown artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v10o-overnight-bias-by-hour-breakdown.spe",
